cpulimit|-----handy-ruler------------------------------------------------------|
cpulimit: cpulimit (Attempts to limit the cpu usage of a process)
cpulimit:
cpulimit: cpulimit is a simple program that attempts to limit the cpu usage of a
cpulimit: process (expressed in percentage, not in cpu time). This is useful to
cpulimit: control batch jobs, when you don't want them to eat too much cpu. It 
cpulimit: does not act on the nice value or other scheduling priority stuff, but
cpulimit: on the real cpu usage. Also, it is able to adapt itself to the overall
cpulimit: system load, dynamically and quickly.
cpulimit:
cpulimit: http://cpulimit.sourceforge.net/
cpulimit: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
